This paper discusses the efficiency of different flaw selection strategies for partial-order causal link (POCL) planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and planning (cs.PL). The paper also presents new experimental results, which may involve machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE) techniques. Additionally, the paper may involve algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for reducing search-space size.
